OL,3,C'Evil' teenager jailed for life for
OL,4,Cmurder of Elianne Andam
OL,6,FSentamu had admitted manslaughter but
OL,7,Fwas found guilty of murder and having
OL,8,Fa blade after a jury rejected his
OL,9,Fclaim that autism affected his ability
OL,10,Fto exercise self-control.
OL,12,FOn Thursday, the teenager, from New
OL,13,FAddington, near Croydon, was jailed
OL,14,Ffor life with a minimum term of 23
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,17,FIn a televised sentencing, Mrs Justice
OL,18,FCheema-Grubb said Elianne, an aspiring
OL,19,Flawyer, was a "hard-working, happy
OL,20,Fgirl" with a "radiant smile".
