OL,4,Cmurder of Elianne Andam
OL,6,FShe said: "Now the music has stopped,
OL,7,Fthe laughter is gone. All that remains
OL,8,Fis a deafening silence."
OL,10,FAddressing Sentamu, she said he had
OL,11,Fruined her life when he killed her
OL,12,Fdaughter in the most "deliberate",
OL,13,F"senseless" and "evil" way.
OL,15,FElianne was full of potential, had
OL,16,Fdreams of becoming a lawyer and would
OL,17,Fhave gone on to do "the greatest
OL,18,Fthings" if her life had not been
OL,19,Ftaken, Mrs Andam said.
