OL,6,FThe day before the killing, he had
OL,7,Fseen the girls at the Whitgift Centre
OL,8,Fwhere they "teased" him and his ex-
OL,9,Fgirlfriend threw water on him.
OL,11,FSeething at the perceived disrespect,
OL,12,Fhe told a friend he could not "let
OL,13,Fthis slide".
OL,15,FThe next day, he donned a mask and
OL,16,Fgloves and armed himself with a
OL,17,Fkitchen knife before a planned meeting
OL,18,Fto hand over his ex-girlfriend's teddy
OL,19,Fbear in exchange for some of his
OL,20,Fclothes.
